Recommended Actions
[Use a shared domain]
Point a custom apex/domain (e.g. aboelo-fitness.de) at Vercel and a subdomain (e.g. api.aboelo-fitness.de) at Render.
In Render, set COOKIE_DOMAIN=.aboelo-fitness.de, CORS_ORIGIN=https://aboelo-fitness.de (and any preview hosts), COOKIE_SAMESITE=none, COOKIE_SECURE=true.
In Vercel, set REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.aboelo-fitness.de/api.
[Redeploy] After configuring DNS and TLS (both platforms automate cert issuance), redeploy backend and frontend so they pick up the new env values.
[Browser reset] Clear site data or open an incognito window, load https://aboelo-fitness.de/login, and confirm cookies appear under Application → Cookies → https://api.aboelo-fitness.de.
[Fallback] If you can’t set up a shared domain yet, proxy API requests through the Vercel app (e.g. using Next.js rewrites or a simple Cloudflare worker) so the browser sees same-origin requests and can keep cookies.

ecommended Actions
[DNS setup]
Log into your domain registrar/DNS host.
Create CNAME records:
fitness → Vercel’s provided target (e.g., cname.vercel-dns.com).
api → Render’s CNAME target for your service (shown under Custom Domains).
[Platform configuration]
In Vercel project settings → Domains, add fitness.aboelo.de. Follow the verification steps; Vercel will automatically provision TLS once DNS propagates.
In Render → your web service → Custom Domains, add api.aboelo.de and complete verification.
[Environment variables]
Render: CORS_ORIGIN=https://fitness.aboelo.de, COOKIE_DOMAIN=.aboelo.de, COOKIE_SAMESITE=none, COOKIE_SECURE=true.
Vercel: REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.aboelo.de/api.
[Deployment]
Redeploy backend and frontend after updating env vars.
Clear browser storage or use an incognito window, then test https://fitness.aboelo.de/login.
Testing
$headers = @{
    "Origin" = "https://fitness.aboelo.de"
}
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://api.aboelo.de/api/auth/csrf" -Headers $headers | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Headers

In the browser, confirm cookies (aboelo_csrf_secret, aboelo_csrf_token, aboelo_auth_token) appear under Application → Cookies for https://api.aboelo.de.
Complete the login flow to verify 200 responses and persistent auth.